Name: REVLITE 247 WOMENS
Description:
The women's New Balance REVlite 247 presents NB's past and future in a single design built for the present. Engineered with all the latest features of New Balance performance footwear, the 247 has notable nods to past models that secured NB's heritage design aesthetic. The 247 is driven to achieve everyday comfort for those constantly on the move. The women's edition features a breathable mesh toe and soft textile sock bootie for a lock-down fit. With optimal, lightweight ventilation, the tonal synthetic overlays are lifted from iconic models like the 576, with a woven tongue label. Underscored by a REVlite 998 midsole, a revised, hexagonal-patterned rubber outsole marries the performance specs of NB's latest with the DNA of a classic.

Name: STAN SMITH
Description:
The Stan Smith from adidas Originals was released in 1973 as the first full leather performance court shoe and has gone on to become an off court icon. Featuring a dimpled outsole for optimal grip and a reinforced heel for achilles support the Stan Smith backed up its understated style with plenty of substance. This shoe is a true icon and is worn around the globe by everyone from the most ardent of sneaker connoisseurs to the recreational tennis player.

Name: AIR PRESTO ESSENTIAL
Description:
Nike Sportswear presents the Air Presto Essential in Navy/Red. A tonal Blue spacer mesh & textile bootie is tempered with a tonal TPU toe, saddle straps and heel counter with a heel loop and floating Presto badge on the tongue. The Phylon midsole features a cushioned Duralon waffle outsole with flex grooves and BRS 1000 rubber heel pods for durable traction. Finished off with a signature contrast Swoosh on the toe vamp and lateral sidewall, the Presto is a bastion of Nike folklore that pioneered limitless design to compliment the latest running technology of its time.

Name: EQT SUPPORT REFINED
Description:
The adidas EQT Support Refined remasters the heritage silhouette from '93. Part of the Equipment series of footwear and apparel circa '93, the Support models were designed to deliver efficient and best-in-class benefits depending on the demands of the athlete. The EQT Support Refined provides nothing but the essentials. A no-sew micro-suede upper with bonded synthetic panelling, mesh and signature webbing tape stripes, enshrine this updated EQT as an original. Laced with Camo accents on the quarter, the contoured tongue and TPU heel/medial support strut remains while a resculpted Gum rubber outsole with Torsion midfoot bar modernizes comfort underfoot.

Name: NMD_R2 PK
Description:
The adidas NMD _R2 emerges between the popular pillars of boost™ and Primeknit. A simplified reminder of the strengths of the Three-Stripes coveted lifestyle design, the streamlined and sleek sequel features a resculpted Boost midsole that removes the familiar forefoot colour blocks and etches their likeness in the heel while conversely enlarging and embellishing the medial midsole insert. Name: AIR MAX ZERO ESSENTIAL
Description:
The Nike Air Max Zero Essential arrives in a classic 'Black & White' colourway. Taken straight from the initial Air Max concept sketches of Tinker Hatfield - the architect of Air- the deconstructed silhouette features a mesh upper with contrast synthetic bonded overlays, Swoosh and a Neoprene tongue bootie with a poly-textile lining. Name: AIR SOCK RACER ULTRA FLYKNIT
Description:
The Nike Air Sock Racer Ultra Flyknit pays homage to itself by draping its uppers in Flyknit – a technology that the original Sock Racer’s stretchy upper was a precursor of. The reliable microfibre straps and buckles remain from the original. Now with a re-tooled sole unit, the already featherweight shoe becomes ultra lightweight, with endless cushioning from ZOOM Air. Siping along the outsole references Nike Free, another major advancement that evolved from the Sock Racer. In keeping with the original’s reputation for being 'Still Crazy After All These Years,' the Air Sock Racer Ultra Flyknit is complete in a subdued, Grey flecked colourway.

Name: ACT 600
Description:
Reebok Classics celebrate their on-court heritage with the 'Hall Of Fame' Pack. Name: LUNARCHARGE PREMIUM
Description:
The Nike LunarCharge Premium blends innovative aspects of Nike's most popular running models for a bold new era. Streamlined for performance and sleek looks, the LunarCharge is executed in a supple Suede and Textile/Neoprene bootie upper with perforated Swoosh detailing on the quarter, suede heel tab for easy on/off and shortened lace stay. Breaking away from tradition and pulsating the beat of the future, the LunarCharge will have you comforted and cushioned, all-day everyday.

Name: X_PLR
Description:
Inspired by adidas' running heritage, the X_PLR presents a modern and fresh take on every-day footwear. Simple, clean looks are conveyed by the breathable mesh bootie upper with synthetic quarter overlays and heel tab. Name: TUBULAR DOOM PK
Description:
The Tubular Doom PK from adidas Originals combines Three-Striped design heritage and innovation with contemporary styled aesthetics. The sock-like Primeknit edition sports a reflective knit upper with wide elastic forefoot and quarter bands that provides a custom fit and avant-garde looks while a textile lacerow and heel wrap provide deconstructed comfort. Name: FREESTYLE HI OG
Description:
Straight from the aerobics class of 1982, the Freestyle High was Reebok's eminent workout shoe for women. It returns today in its original fabrication with close attention paid to the original tooling of the high-top. A supple, garment leather upper laminated with a nylon backing for durability is perforated for breathability. Two velcro hook and loop enclosures ensures a custom fit while heritage woven labels on the quarter and tongue recall the original era. With a simple construction and no fuss attitude, the Freestyle Hi is built with comfort and durability in mind.

Name: AIR MAX 95 JACQUARD
Description:
The Air Max 95 Jacquard realises the potential of the most ambitious Air Max model of the 90s. Utilising the latest innovations in construction and comfort, Nike have stripped the game-changing Air Max 95 silhouette with their Ultra initiative; finding efficiencies in weight and comfort by deconstructing the original design. The final result witnesses a woven jacquard upper with Flywire support struts securing the midsole and Laces for a custom fit. Meanwhile, the midsole has been cored out with a reduced weight, uncompromising the signature visible AIR cushioning in the forefoot and heel.

Name: HYPERVENOM 3
Description:

Agile and form-fitting, the Free Hypervenom 3 brings football inspired lines off the pitch for incredible comfort.

Name: ZOOM MERCURIAL FLYKNIT
Description:
The Nike Zoom Mercurial Flyknit exemplifies the latest design innovation and ingenuity from the Swoosh. The Mercurial football boot transitions the pitch to the pavement with bold effect. The elevated silhouette receives a split Black & White Flyknit upper with an updated woven Flywire forefoot, V-Notch bootie structure and a coated suede heel wrap. Providing optimal ventilation, the Flyknit upper also features an enlarged welded Swoosh from the toe to the anterior side of the shoe and 'Nike F.C' wordmark on the ankle. The lightweight topside is underscored by the ZOOM Air Spiridon Phylon Midsole with ZOOM Air filled carbon rubber pods on the outsole providing responsive cushioning, traction and stability.

Name: LUNAR MAGISTA II FLYKNIT
Description:
The Lunar Magista II Flyknit is a prime example of the latest design innovation and ingenuity from Nike. Continuing the Nike F.C trend of emulating pitch-side heroes for the streets, the latest Magista II debuts in an updated material and utilitarian update. The elevated silhouette receives a tightly woven Flyknit upper with an extended bootie/tongue/collar. The upper also features an embroidered Swoosh, sock-like fit and a coated suede heel loop for easier on/off. The premium topside is underscored by a speckled Lunar midsole with carbon rubber pod tread with flex grooves, promoting natural motion and lightweight comfort.

Name: AIR SOCK RACER ULTRA FLYKNIT
Description:
The Nike Air Sock Racer Ultra Flyknit pays homage to itself by draping its uppers in Flyknit – a precursor of the original Sock Racer’s stretchy sock-like upper. The reliable microfibre straps and buckles remain from the original for a lock-down, customisable fit. Now with a re-tooled sole unit, the already featherweight shoe becomes ultra lightweight, with endless cushioning from ZOOM Air. Siping along the outsole references Nike Free comfort, while in keeping with the original’s reputation for being 'Still Crazy After All These Years,' the Air Sock Racer Ultra Flyknit is complete in a Black & White flecked colourway.

Name: SAMBA
Description:
The adidas Originals Samba stands out as a legacy design of the Trefoil. Pitch boot turned street staple, the Samba returns to its roots with heritage street styling. A smooth leather upper features contrasting textured suede on the toe with contrast Three-Stripes and heel tab for a classic look. The vintage compressed foam tongue sports bluebird Trefoil branding while a bold Gold-foil quarter callout completes this historical package, Finished with a gum-rubber midsole with retro detailing and tread, the Samba is back to rule the streets.

Name: AIR FOOTSCAPE WOVEN NM
Description:
The Nike Air Footscape Woven NM arrives in a Special Edition make-up this season. Taking the evolutionary 1996 Footscape silhouette with asymmetrical lacing and updating the specs, the latest iteration features articulated Ripstop paneling woven by nylon webbing. Finer details include a plush textile liner and  embroidered heel and tongue branding. The tactile upper is secured to a cushioned Footscape midsole with flex grooves that supports Natural Motion and rubber pod traction for grip on the streets.

Name: AIR ZOOM LWP
Description:
The Nike Air Zoom LWP elevates the original 1995 iteration with updated specs and an OG colourway. Standing for Light Weight Performance, the Air Zoom LWP features a mesh bootie construction with reinforced TPU bonded overlays. A padded micro-mesh collar and neoprene tongue are complete with a nylon heel tab for easier on/off transition. The signature of the shoe lies in it's sculpted Phylon midsole with contrast Zoom Air pods in the rear and forefoot exposed through the deconstructed outsole. Secured by Brio cable eyelets and cotton cord laces, the Air Zoom LWP accelerates the modern comfort of the Swoosh.

Name: SOCK DART
Description:
The Nike Sock Dart presents an avant-garde yet sleek look in classic Black/White. Updated for a premium touch, this version features a circular knit forefoot and slick Nylon collar and heel on the upper. With a TPU toe cap, the foot is cradled by an articulated, lightweight foam midsole with flex grooves and carbon rubber pod tread. Signature elements of the design lie in the customisable perforated silicon midfoot strap that provides a lock-down fit and a rubber heel pod that sports a mini-swoosh logo. Lightweight, breathable and flexible, the Sock Dart is a signpost of Nike's innovative comfort.

Name: AIR MAX ZERO ESSENTIAL
Description:
The Nike Air Max Zero Essential is taken straight from the initial Air Max concept sketches of Tinker Hatfield. The architect of Air, Tinker's design presents a deconstructed silhouette that features a mesh upper with tonal synthetic bonded overlays, contrast Swoosh and Neoprene tongue bootie with a poly-textile lining. Plastic D-lace eyelets and a bonded tongue logo placard are underscored by a cored out, featherweight Ultra midsole with improved flexibility and increased visible AIR in infrared. Fleshed out on paper some 30 years ago, enjoy the original concept of AIR come to life with the Air Max Zero.

Name: AIR PRESTO ESSENTIAL
Description:
Nike Sportswear presents the Air Presto Essential in classic Black & White. A tonal Black spacer mesh & textile bootie is tempered with a tonal TPU toe, saddle straps and heel counter with a heel loop and floating Presto badge on the tongue. The Phylon midsole features a cushioned Duralon waffle outsole with flex grooves and BRS 1000 rubber heel pods for durable traction. Finished off with a signature tonal Swoosh on the toe vamp and lateral sidewall, the Presto is a bastion of Nike folklore that pioneered limitless design to compliment the latest running technology of its time.

Name: AIR MAX 90 ULTRA 2.0 FLYKNIT
Description:
The fabled Air Max 90 legacy evolves with the Ultra 2.0 Flyknit edition, debuting the Air Max legend in Flyknit. A combination woven and bonded materials, as well as a cored-out midsole, delivers iconic AIR with lightweight, optimal ventilation. This 'Triple-White' Flyknit colourway features Hyperfused TPU accents with a bonded mudguard and Swoosh on the upper. Complete with an Ultra midsole with re-envisioned visible AIR bag and Phylon injected forefoot, the Flyknit 90 sports a compressed textile mesh tongue and contoured sockliner for comfort and breathability.

Name: REVLITE 247
Description:

Engineered with all the latest features of New Balance performance footwear, the 'Dawn Til Dusk' Pack 247 is driven to achieve everyday comfort in premium finishes. Name: TUBULAR SHADOW
Description:
The unisex adidas Tubular Shadow captures the avant-garde design spirit of the contemporary Tubular series. Constructed of an asymmetrical upper with premium flat knit textile across the medial and lateral sides, the Shadow installs an innovative contoured 'Burrito' enclosure tongue for a lock-down fit. The modern design also features an S-curve heel cup and an Ortholite® insole for long-lasting comfort. Underscored by a revised and rippled EVA midsole, the Shadow breaks new ground as the simplest expression of adidas sport-style.

Description:

Name: All Star High X Nike Flyknit
Description:
The Chuck Taylor All Star X Nike Flyknit arrives at the intersection of timeless style and innovation. A courteous recognition of a century-old design, Converse's parent Nike have afforded the All Star High the modernity of Flyknit. Dressing up the high top, the Flyknit edition features a complete woven knit upper with transparent TPU enforced toe cap and Lunarlon cushioned insole inside the traditional rubber midsole. With an embroidered All-Star patch logo, the benefits of the knitted upper allow for strength, flexibility and ventilation that ascends the Chuck's fit and feel to all new heights.

Name: TUBULAR DOOM SOCK
Description:
The Tubular Doom Sock from adidas Originals combines Three-Striped design heritage and innovation with contemporary styled aesthetics. The sock-like, engineered mesh edition sports a heathered knit bootie that provides a sock-like fit and avant-garde looks. Name: ZOKU RUNNER ULTRAKNIT WOMENS
Description:
Reebok unveil the women's Zoku Ultra Knit in soft powder Blue. Paying homage to the storied hallmarks of Reebok's running innovations and milestones, the Zoku captures the spirit of 1979's Aztec Runner in style but updates the ingredients of form. A woven Ultra Knit upper features perforations for breathability and zones for strength while a tonal TPU Vector is sewn on the quarter. Connected to a synthetic heel wrap with debossed Reebok wordmark, a heel loop ensures a smooth transition on and off. Sitting atop a tonal DMX rubber midsole with non-marking rubber inserts for traction, the Zoku Ultra Knit combines Reebok heritage with the latest innovations in construction and comfort.

Name: APTARE ESSENTIAL

Name: AIR ZOOM MARIAH FLYKNIT RACER WOMENS
Description:
The Nike Women's Air Zoom Mariah Flyknit Racer presents the next evolution of Nike's commitment to speed and comfort. Taking cues from the Flyknit Racer, Nike have retrofitted the vintage Mariah roadrunner in fabrication and style. Crafted from a single piece of Flyknit, zonal density allows stretch around the collar, support at the heel and breathability on the toe. With brio cable eyelets providing a lock-down fit, the Mariah Flyknit fuses a cursive TPU heel-cage onto the rear for additional support and comfort. The lightweight blown midsole features a unit of Air Zoom in the footbed for everyday cushioning while a heel loop permits easy entry into the Flyknit bootie.

The ZX Flux from adidas Originals is the original running inspired silhouette featuring a micro mesh one-piece upper, moulded heel cage, on top of the classic ZX 8000 sole unit with TORSION® midfoot bar. The shoe also utilises the adidas SoftCell technology in the heel for superior impact protection. The ZX Flux has sleek minimal lines and iconic elements maintaining the ZX pedigree. An exceptional example of past and future tech coming together.

Name: AIR MAX THEA
Description:
The Nike women's Air Max Thea has been seasonally updated. A lightweight sneaker with a sleek, low cut profile, the latest version of the Air Max Thea features a mesh upper with Hyperfused synthetic overlays, a textured and perforated heel wrap, heel loop and neoprene tongue. Maximising lightweight breathability for comfort, the Thea is equipped with a moulded Phylon midsole with visible AIR cushioning in the heel. With contrasting Swoosh detailing, tonal laces and a plush Solarsoft insole, the Air Max Thea provides understated style and great versatility.

Name: SUPERSTAR
Description:
The Superstar is THE iconic silhouette of the adidas Originals﻿ back catalogue. Resplendent in it's signature low top, the upper is clad in an action leather with contrasting Three-Stripes, heel tab and Goldleaf tongue label and side print callout. Attached is the trademark stitched rubber cupsole featuring the infamous rubber shell-toe that has since become a global cultural icon. The Superstar from adidas Originals has been everywhere and back again - this time, even more versatile and relevant than ever.

Name: GAZELLE
Description:
The Gazelle II from adidas Originals recalls the heritage styling of the Trefoil circa 1968. The updated II Edition is crafted for the streets of today, with a premium tonal leather make-up from heel to toe with contrasting Goldleaf callout on the quarter. A blown rubber midsole and outsole provides simple durability and traction while the synthetic lining and textile backed, stamped tongue provides sleek comfort.

Name: ADILETTE
Description: The Classic adilette slide from adidas Originals arrives just in time for the warmer seasons. Originally introduced in 1972, delivering off-field relief for touring football teams and their fans, the adilette brings Trefoil folklore to the contemporary slide phenomenon. Making use of a solid rubber sole with moulded PU footbed and a durable synthetic upper for comfort, this slide will have you covered in the wet or dry. Slide your foot into adidas history this summer.

Name: CLUB C 85
Description:
Reebok dig deep into their strong tradition of on-court footwear and bring-back the Club Champion from 1985. Now dubbed the Club C, the simple court shoe features a gloving tonal leather upper, Grass Green Woven Label saddle & tongue branding, Cotton-Poly Cloth lining and Nylon tongue. Underscored by a stitched cupsole with injected EVA for comfort and a high-abrasion tread, the Club C is back for the win.

Name: STAN SMITH
Description:
The Stan Smith from adidas Originals was released in 1973 as the first full leather performance court shoe and has gone on to become an off court icon. Featuring a dimpled outsole for optimal grip and a reinforced heel for achilles support the Stan Smith backed up its understated style with plenty of substance. The trademark stripes have been replaced by perforations and this is the original colourway of all white with a green heel tab and Stan himself smiling out from the tongue. This shoe is a true icon and is worn around the globe by everyone from the most ardent of sneaker connoisseurs to the recreational tennis player.

Name: EQT SUPPORT REFINED
Description:
The adidas EQT Support Refined remasters the heritage silhouette from '93. Part of the Equipment series of footwear and apparel circa '93, the Support models were designed to deliver efficient and best-in-class benefits depending on the demands of the athlete. The EQT Support Refined provides nothing but the essentials. A no-sew micro-suede upper with bonded synthetic panelling, mesh and signature webbing tape stripes, enshrine this updated EQT as an original. Laced with Camo accents on the quarter, the contoured tongue and TPU heel/medial support strut remains while a resculpted Gum rubber outsole with Torsion midfoot bar modernizes comfort underfoot.

Name: AIR MAX ZERO WOMENS

Name: AIR MAX 90 ULTRA 2.0 WOMENS FLYKNIT
Description:
The women's Air Max 90 Ultra 2.0 Flyknit presents the updated Air Max legend in an 'Oreo' colourway. Name: All Star High X Nike Flyknit
Description:
The Chuck Taylor All Star X Nike Flyknit arrives a the intersection of timeless style and innovation. A courteous recognition of a century-old design, Converse's parent Nike have afforded the All Star High the modernity of Flyknit. Dressing up the high top, the Flyknit edition features a complete woven knit upper with transparent TPU enforced toe cap, Lunarlon cushioned insole and embroidered All-Star Logo. Benefits of the knitted upper allow for strength, flexibility and ventilation that ascends the Chuck's fit and feel to all new heights.

Name: REVLITE 247 WOMENS
Description:
The women's New Balance REVlite 247 presents NB's past and future in a single design. Name: NMD_R2
Description:
The adidas NMD _R2 emerges as a simplified reminder of the strengths of the Three-Stripes coveted lifestyle design. The streamlined and sleek sequel features a resculpted Boost midsole that removes the familiar forefoot colour blocks and etches their likeness in the heel while conversely enlarging and embellishing the medial midsole insert. The engineered textile upper weaves in a unique 'glitch streak' pattern and texture, with a an exposed printed heel loop threaded through the rear heel tab. Bold with bonded Three-Stripes, the NMD_R2 distinguishes itself from the pack, racing forward into modernity just as quickly as it entered the streets of today.

Name: EQT SUPPORT ADV
Description:
The adidas EQT Support ADV remixes the Support edition from '93 for the streets of today. Honouring and defying the original, the 2017 Support ADV arrives in a tonal palette of classic Black & White. The quality of the original carries over to the ADV with premium materials and purposeful construction. A textile mesh bootie is bonded and stitched to a sport suede quarter and heel wrap, with signature EQT webbing Three-Stripes cradling the foot. Finished with a luxurious, laser-cut milled leather heel cage and and tongue label, the ADV is comforted by a textile lining. The core design of the PU midsole is also recast in a sculpted, slimline unit with contrasting Three-Striped decals carried over. Flexible and lightweight, the new original aims to be as iconic as its predecessor.

Name: EQT SUPPORT REFINED
Description:
The adidas EQT Support Refined remasters the heritage silhouette from '93. Part of the Equipment series of footwear and apparel circa '93, the Support models were designed to deliver efficient and best-in-class benefits depending on the demands of the athlete. The EQT Support Refined provides nothing but the essentials. A premium nubuck leather upper with stitched synthetic panelling, mesh and milled leather hits enshrine this modern EQT in class and comfort. Laced with tonal accents on the lace webbing, the contoured mesh tongue and laser-cut, milled leather heel/medial support strut remains while a resculpted rubber outsole with Torsion midfoot bar modernizes comfort underfoot.

Name: ONE STAR
Description:

First arriving on the scene in 1974 and cementing itself amongst underground subcultures in the 90s, the latest re-release replicates the OG with aplomb. Name: FLYKNIT RACER
Description:
The Nike Flyknit Racer debuts on Hype DC shelves with the classic 'Oreo' edition. Crafted in a single layer of Flyknit, the woven and tensile sheath wraps around your foot for an adaptive, breathable and lightweight fit. Name: BASKET HEART
Description:
The PUMA women's Basket Heart evolves the legendary low-top with a flourish. The patent leather upper with Gold-foil wordmarks features a remixed lacerow with large eyelets catering to the enlarged, and thick woven Cotton laces. With a bold statement on the top, the monochrome colourway also sports a textile lining and insole for comfort and with a custom printed insole. Complete with a vintage rubber cupsole, the women's Basket Heart breaks new ground with a loud lace-up option that breaks all the rules.

Name: CAMPUS WOMENS
Description:
The adidas Campus is an understated model of the Trefoil's back catalogue. Arriving just after the Gazelle, the Campus made moves in the shadow of the Stan Smith and Superstar, riding underground popularity through the 80s and 90s. Crafted in buttery, heavy slub suede in a dusty pantone, the women's Campus sports familiar contrasting Three- Stripes and heel tab with a synthetic leather lining. With cotton laces, no-liner branded suede tongue and complementing quarter callouts, the campus is underscored by a rubber cupsole with heritage tread outsole- the key ingredients that made the Campus a mover and shaker on and off the court.

Name: AIR MAX JEWELL WOMENS
Description:
The Nike women's Air Max Jewell is the latest entry in a strong lineage of contemporary classics crafted for women. The Air Max Jewell is presented with mesh upper and synthetic bonded detailing, executed in a classic Air Max shape borrowing from the Tuned Air models of the late 90s and early 2000s. The Air Max Jewel also features a printed contrast Swoosh, TPU toe cap and unique S-cut Phylon midsole with a tempered shank plate and visible Air bag in the segmented heel. Complete with heritage inspired rubber waffle tread, the Air Max Jewell sets a new, fashionable standard in all-day, everyday comfort.

Name: AIR SOCK RACER ULTRA FLYKNIT WOMENS
Description:
The Nike Women's Air Sock Racer Ultra Flyknit pays homage to itself by draping its uppers in Flyknit – a technology that the original Sock Racer’s stretchy upper was a precursor of 
 - while the reliable microfibre straps and buckles remain from the original. Now with a re-tooled sole unit, the already featherweight shoe becomes ultra lightweight, with endless cushioning from ZOOM Air and siping along the outsole for improved flexibility. In keeping with the original’s reputation for being 'Still Crazy After All These Years,' the Air Sock Racer Ultra Flyknit is complete in a Pink & Grey flecked colourway.

Name: OLD SKOOL
Description:
The Vans Old Skool was first known as Vans #36 model. The original silhouette with the contrasting side or 'Jazz' stripe, the unmistakable hallmark touch capped off the hard-wearing canvas low-top. Name: AIR PRESTO WOMENS
Description:
The Nike Women's Presto presents a luxe 'Orewood' take on the T-Shirt for your feet. Constructed of a breathable mesh upper with tonal TPU lace struts, toe cap and heel wrap, the Presto features a bootie construction that hugs the foot for a custom fit. A product of Nike's Alpha Project circa 2000, the Presto is equipped with a unique Phylon midsole that combines Nike's heritage Waffle tread with a tonal Duralon rubber for a flexible and responsive feel every step.

Name: AIR MAX THEA
Description:
The Nike women's Air Max Thea continues its role as the Queen of Air. A lightweight sneaker with a sleek, low cut profile, the latest version of the Air Max Thea features a mesh upper with Hyperfused synthetic overlays, a croc-textured and perforated heel wrap, textile heel loop and mesh tongue. Maximising lightweight breathability for comfort, the Thea is equipped with a moulded Phylon midsole with visible AIR cushioning in the heel. With contrast Swoosh detailing, rounded laces and a plush Solarsoft backed insole, the Air Max Thea provides understated style and great versatility for everyday wear.

Name: LODEN WOMENS
Description:
The Nike Women's Loden presents the latest silhouette designed for all day everyday comfort. Inspired by Nike's iconic Air Rift model, the Loden elevates the bold original design for everyday wear with simplified lines, comfort points and a sung fit. A textile and mesh upper features neoprene webbing, a hidden lace system and a tongue and heel pull loop for easy on/off. Underfoot, a lightweight Pyhlon pod-like structure is capped off with Gum rubber hits on the heel and toe for extra durability. An embroidered Swoosh on the quarter complete's the Loden's design with simplicity in mind.

Name: SOCK DART GRADE SCHOOL
Description:
The Nike Sock Dart GS introduces minimised dimensions of the deconstructed design. A descendant of the Presto the Sock Dart sports avant-garde looks in White & Pink. Name: GEL LYTE V NS
Description:
The Gel Lyte V 'No Sew' highlights the latest progression of ASICS' iconic road runner in an OG inspired colourway. The mixed synthetic and enclosed mesh upper has been heat bonded together with laminated Tiger stripes for a seamless look. Name: JANOSKI
Description:
The Janoski from Nike Skateboarding﻿ is the Stefan Janoski pro model that draws from both classic skate and nautical influences. This Original make-up features a durable canvas upper, poly-suede lining and coated cotton laces. The autoclave construction yields a vulcanized midsole fused with a classic gum rubber tread while a ZOOM Air Unit lies in the footbed of the insole. A contemporary classic of skate, the Janoski provides comfort and traction on and off the board while being equiped with best-in-class impact protection for a clean, minimal skate aesthetic.

Name: JANOSKI MAX
Description:

The sock-like, bootie construction with minimal seams sits atop an updated midsole, crafted in lightweight Phylon. The new midsole features flex grooves at the forefoot for a natural motion feel and a visible Max Air unit in the heel, providing superior comfort and impact protection. With signature Nike SB lines and shape, the Janoski Max elevates the signature silhouette into a comfortable shoe for the streets.

Lightweight and flexible, the Sock Dart arrives as a signpost of Nike's innovative deconstructed comfort.

Name: DESERT BOOT III
Description:
Originally designed by Nathan Clark in 1950 as a gentlemen's and officer's choice of footwear for R & R - the Desert Boot III by Clarks Originals celebrates 65 years of timeless design and style. This iconic 2 piece mid-cut chukka boot features a suede leather for a pull-up texture that will soften in age with its own patina. This is complimented by the iconic crepe rubber outsole for long-term comfort and durability. The perfect example of simplicity and craftsmanship, the Desert boot has traversed culture and fashion over its decorated history, arriving just in time for a new chapter - where will you take it?

Name: AIR MAX ZERO ESSENTIAL
Description:

Name: AIR MAX ZERO ESSENTIAL
Description:
The Nike Air Max Zero Essential arrives in a classic 'Triple-Black' colourway. Taken straight from the initial Air Max concept sketches of Tinker Hatfield - the architect of Air- the deconstructed silhouette features a mesh upper with tonal synthetic bonded overlays, Swoosh and a Neoprene tongue bootie with a poly-textile lining. Plastic lace eyelets and a bonded tongue logo placard are underscored by a cored out, featherweight Ultra midsole with improved flexibility and increased visible AIR. Fleshed out on paper over 30 years ago, enjoy the original concept of AIR come to life with the Air Max Zero.

Name: AIR MAX 1 ULTRA 2.0 ESSENTIAL
Description:
Nike Sportswear's Air Max 1 Ultra 2.0 Essential takes the original Nike Air Max shoe with visible Air to all new heights. With a streamlined execution on the upper and midsole, the lightweight silhouette redefines the signature elements. A hyperfused synthetic and mesh upper is equipped with a micro-mesh lining and bonded Swoosh & tongue branding. This sits atop a reduced and re-engineered midsole, with a larger, more exposed air unit on the outsole and flexible forefoot design on the midfoot. The Air Max 1 Ultra brings together past and present technologies to deliver the newest iteration of the original Air Max experience.

Name: CLUB WORKOUT
Description:
The Reebok Club Workout presents a hybrid cross-trainer from the Classic imprint. Combining the Workout upper with a Club C midsole, the Club Workout is quintessentially classic. A soft, garment leather upper has been applied with a H-strap and reinforced heel providing added durability and stability. A nylon tongue sports heritage, pinpoint embroidery and woven labels that expand to the H-strap. The rubber midsole is offered in a stitched cupsole style reminiscent of the Club C while the Club Workout is finished with classic terry towelling on the lining to press its cult credentials amongst discerning fans of the label.

Name: AIR MAX ZERO
Description:
As part of the 'Gold Metallic' Premium Pack, the Nike Air Max Zero assumes the coveted colourway made famous by the Air Max '97. Taken straight from the initial Air Max concept sketches of Tinker Hatfield - the architect of Air- the deconstructed Air Max Zero silhouette features a mesh upper with synthetic bonded overlays, Gold Swoosh and a Neoprene tongue bootie with a poly-textile lining. TPU lace eyelets and a bonded tongue logo placard are underscored by a cored out, featherweight Ultra Air midsole with improved flexibility and increased visible AIR. Fleshed out on paper some 30 years ago, enjoy the original concept of AIR come to life with the Air Max Zero.

Name: AIR ZOOM BLAZER MID XT
Description:
The Nike SB Air Zoom Blazer Mid XT presents a remix of the legendary Swoosh basketball silhouette first released in 1972. Featuring a premium suede upper, leather vintage cut Swoosh and nylon mesh tongue, the XT has un updated toe-piece tooling and wrap for added protection. Name: STAN SMITH
Description:
The Stan Smith from adidas Originals was released in 1973 as the first full leather performance court shoe and has gone on to become an off court icon. Featuring a dimpled outsole for optimal grip and a reinforced heel for achilles support, the Stan Smith backed up its understated style with plenty of substance. The trademark stripes have been replaced by perforations while an all-white leather upper sports a contrasting Red heel tab with Stan himself smiling out from the tongue. This shoe is a true icon and is worn around the globe by everyone from the most ardent of sneaker connoisseurs to the recreational tennis player.

Name: REVLITE 247
Description:
The New Balance REVlite 247 presents NB's past and future in a single design built for the present. Engineered with all the latest features of New Balance performance footwear, the 247 has notable nods to past models that secured NB's heritage design aesthetic. The 247 is driven to achieve everyday comfort for those constantly on the move. A breathable mesh toe is secured to a textile sock bootie for a lock-down fit. With optimal, lightweight ventilation, the tonal synthetic overlays are lifted from iconic models like the 576, with a woven tongue label. Underscored by a REVlite 998 midsole, a revised, hexagonal-patterned rubber outsole marries the performance specs of NB's latest with the DNA of a classic.

Name: CLUB WORKOUT
Description:
The Reebok Club Workout presents a hybrid cross-trainer from the Classic imprint. Combining the Workout upper with a Club C midsole, the Club Workout is quintessentially classic. A soft, garment leather upper has been applied with a H-strap and reinforced heel providing added durability and stability. A nylon tongue sports heritage, pinpoint embroidery and woven labels that expand to the H-strap. The rubber midsole is offered in a stitched cupsole style reminiscent of the Club C while the Club Workout is finished with classic terry towelling on the lining to press its cult credentials amongst discerning fans of the label.

Name: ERA

Name: All Star High X Nike Flyknit
Description:
The Chuck Taylor All Star X Nike Flyknit arrives at the intersection of timeless style and innovation. A courteous recognition of a century-old design, Converse's parent Nike have afforded the All Star High the modernity of Flyknit. Dressing up the high top, the Flyknit edition features a complete woven knit upper with transparent TPU enforced toe cap and Lunarlon cushioned insole inside the traditional rubber midsole. With an embroidered All-Star patch logo, the benefits of the knitted upper allow for strength, flexibility and ventilation that ascends the Chuck's fit and feel to all new heights.

Sporting the Spezial midsole in white with signature port holes on the toe and raised support in the rear, the Busenitz is complete with a micro-mesh sockliner for comfort and breathability.

Name: ZOOM P-ROD X

Name: MEXICO 66
Description:
The Mexico 66 from Onitsuka Tiger was first introduced in 1966 and made history at the 1968 Olympic games in Mexico. The simple leather clad upper of the Mexico design features suede toe and heel detailing with a loose leather heel tab finishing off this vintage silhouette.

Name: DELEGATION
Description:
The Delegation from Onitsuka Tiger was first introduced in 1968 as the off-track equivalent of the infamous Mexico '66 design. Faithfully manufactured to the specifications of the original, the Delegation is constructed of a premium suede upper with iconic Tiger Stripes, Nylon padded tongue and micro-mesh lining. The Delegation sits atop a vintage Gum Rubber midsole with court-side foxing and heritage tread. With a nod to its predecessor in the form of a 'Mexico' callout on the quarter panel, the Delegation is complete with casual styling and a simple heel tab for easy on/off.

Name: ALL STAR II HIGH
Description:
The Converse All Star II High presents an updated revision of the timeless sneaker. Constructed of a durable split-cloth canvas, this Triple-Black release features upgraded comfort points for an elevated fit and feel. The liner and new padded tongue have been updated with a micro-suede for comfort while a drop-in Nike Lunarlon® insole delivers the latest in lightweight cushioning. Subtle detailing such as pinstripes on the vulcanized midsole, embroidered medial 'All-Star' woven patch, 'Converse' embossed metal eyelets and premium stitching through out completes this 'under-the-hood' revision of the 98 Year-old design.

Name: PORTMORE II
Description:
The Nike SB Portmore II presents the latest sequel to a modern classic in fit and comfort. Constructed of a durable canvas, the 3 piece upper consists of minimal stitching and simple overlays with a retro-cut Swoosh. Meanwhile, the autoclave assembly of parts enhances the herringbone rubber sole, offering greater traction, support and board-feel - no matter the terrain. A minimal, sleek look with a modern fit and Solarsoft cushioned insoles sets the Portmore II up to deliver the latest in classic Nike SB skate tech.

Name: All Star High Leather
Description: The All Star High from Converse was initially introduced in 1917 and has maintained its style and substance ever since. The iconic silhouette features a full-grain leather split-cloth upper, metal eyelets and a traditional vulcanised sole with a rubber toe cap and vintage rubber tread. With the classic All Star logo on the medial sidewall a nod to its heritage, these casual shoes continue to blaze their own path ceaselessly into the future.

Name: JESSE-C
Description:
The Suicoke Jesse-C presents a simplified design from the Japanese performance sandal manufacturer. A cross-strap forefoot and hook & loop heel wrap features Nylon tape detailing with a synthetic fibre backed heel. Providing a custom fit and support the Jesse-C is complete with a woven label on the backstrap and a slim Suicoke EVA footbed, with articulated comfort points for cushioning and a Vibram® Morflex sole for best-in-class comfort, traction and durability.

Name: DEPA
Description:
The Suicoke Depa presents a simple, utilitarian design from the Japanese performance sandal manufacturer. The Depa's low profile features two Nylon tape forefoot and back Velcro straps are connected by a single band with a TPU joint for tensile strength and form. Complete with a woven label on the anterior band and synthetic fibre heel piece, the Depa-C has the Suicoke signature EVA footbed, with articulated comfort points for cushioning and a Vibram® Morflex sole for best-in-class comfort, traction and durability.
